Kaffara Episode 23 - [Eng Sub] - Ali Ansari - Laiba Khan - Zoya Nasir - 19th August 2024 - HAR PAL GEO

Sitara, a lively orphan living with her brother, aunt, and uncle, finds joy in life's small things despite her aunt's poor treatment. Her aunt keeps her around because she has a share in the family's property.
Salar, the son of a wealthy businessman, is passionate about photography, which often earns him criticism from his family. With a pure heart, Salar is known for evading his responsibilities.
At her cousin's wedding, Sitara wrongly assumes Salar is the photographer. Salar develops a soft spot for Sitara after seeing how poorly she is treated. However, due to a conspiracy, objections arise about their closeness. Salar, once again, avoids the issue, leaving Sitara to face doubts from her own family.

snippet.title: Mahindra Thar Roxx 2WD AX7L- â‚¹20.4 lakh | Real-life review
snippet.description:
Namaste friends, please LIKE & SUBSCRIBE :)

The Mahindra Thar Roxx is a five-door variant of the Thar SUV, launched by Mahindra & Mahindra in India on August 15, 2024. This model is designed to offer additional space and modern features while maintaining the off-road capabilities for which the Thar line-up is known. The Thar Roxx is built on Mahindra's new M_Glyde platform. It gets Indiaâ€™s First Crawl Smart Assist and IntelliTurn which can conquer tough terrains and tight turns with ease for superior off-road maneuverability. It also gets expansive Panoramic Skyroof which provides a wide open-air view, enhancing the sense of space in every drive. Also equipped with Harman Kardon 9-speaker system with QuantumLogic and Twin HD screens. #Mahindra #TharRoxx #MahindraTharRoxx

Petrol: 1997 cc, Inline-4 cylinder,  G20 mStallion engine with Turbo Petrol Direct Injection (TGDI), Automatic- 174 HP Power, 380 Nm Torque, Manual- 159 HP Power, 330 Nm Torque, Approx. 12 kmpl Average, 57 litre Fuel Tank, 6-speed Manual or 6-speed Aisin Torque Converter Automatic Transmission

Diesel: 2184 cc, Inline-4 cylinder, D22 mHawk engine with 1600 bar Common Rail Direct Injection Technology, RWD- 150 HP Power, 330 Nm Torque, 4WD- 172 HP Power, 370 Nm Torque, Approx. 15 kmpl Average, 57 litre Fuel Tank, 6-speed Manual or 6-speed Aisin Torque Converter Automatic Transmission

4 Variants: MX1, MX3, AX3L, MX5, AX5L, AX7L

2 Upholsteries: Black Fabric, Beige Leatherette

3 Wheels: 18 inch Steel, 18 inch Alloy, 19 inch Diamond Cut Alloy

7 Colours: Black, Blue, Grey, Brown, Red, White, Stealth Black

Price range (Excluding 4WD): Rs. 12.99 lakh - Rs. 20.49 lakh (Ex-showroom, Delhi)

Jaan Nisar Digitally Presented by Happilac Paints

7th Sky Entertainmentâ€™s mega project, Jaan Nisar, is the most awaited drama serial of the year.
The highly anticipated project marks the return of the successful on-screen couple of Danish Taimoor and Hiba Bukhari in an unforgettable love story that will steal your heart.

Nosherwan Ghaznavi, a wealthy young man, faces a pivotal moment in his life after his brother's death. This tragedy burdens Nosherwan Ghaznavi with numerous responsibilities, which he reluctantly accepts, only to find them later proving detrimental. However, his life takes a transformative turn upon meeting Dua, falling in love with her at first sight, but it places him at a critical juncture with his responsibilities.

Dua, a beautiful girl from a humble background, is raised by her parents alongside her two sisters. Despite her innocence, fate subjects Dua to a string of misfortunes before encountering Nosherwan Ghaznavi. However, their meeting completely changes their lives.

Will Nowsherwan Ghaznavi find love? What challenges will he face in balancing his duties and his love for Dua? Will his responsibilities jeopardize his love for Dua? What past events have shaped Dua's life, and will they resurface to trouble her? Will Dua return Nowsherwan Ghaznaviâ€™s love?

You can check it out here for the village style recipes .

Kaffara Episode 22 - [Eng Sub] - Ali Ansari - Laiba Khan - Zoya Nasir - 18th August 2024 - HAR PAL GEO

Sitara, a lively orphan living with her brother, aunt, and uncle, finds joy in life's small things despite her aunt's poor treatment. Her aunt keeps her around because she has a share in the family's property.
Salar, the son of a wealthy businessman, is passionate about photography, which often earns him criticism from his family. With a pure heart, Salar is known for evading his responsibilities.
At her cousin's wedding, Sitara wrongly assumes Salar is the photographer. Salar develops a soft spot for Sitara after seeing how poorly she is treated. However, due to a conspiracy, objections arise about their closeness. Salar, once again, avoids the issue, leaving Sitara to face doubts from her own family.
Can Sitara prove sheâ€™s not guilty? Will Salar help her avoid further mistreatment? Will her family support Sitara? Can Salar show he genuinely cares? Will there be more plots against Sitara?

snippet.title: Worldâ€™s Deadliest Battle | The Mahabharat Series | Ep 1 | Vikram Aditya  | Telugu
snippet.description:
Welcome to the first episode in our series on the Mahabharat, one of the greatest epics ever written. In this drama, we delve into the profound truth that there are no purely good or bad people, only good and bad circumstances.
In this episode, we explore Vyasa's visionary experience that led to the creation of this timeless epic. Discover how Vyasa, after dividing the Vedas, received a haunting vision of a catastrophic warâ€”The Mahabharat. Disturbed and eager to document every detail, Vyasa chose the only being capable of keeping up with his narration, Lord Ganesha, to write down the untold story of his descendants.
Our storytelling is not just about revisiting ancient tales; it's about extracting timeless wisdom to confront modern challenges. This episode lays the foundation for understanding the Mahabharat's depth, where virtue and vice intertwine, revealing critical life lessons.

About Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah:
----------------------------------------------------------------------
The show is inspired by the famous humorous column 'Duniya Ne Undha Chasma' by the eminent Gujarati writer Mr Tarak Mehta. This story evolves around happenings in "Gokuldham Co-operative Society" and covers topical issues that are socially relevant. The show predominantly revolves around 'Jethalaal' (Dilip Joshi), an uneducated Gujarati businessman. Your 'Taarak Mehta' (Sailesh Lodha), is his neighbour. 'Jethalaal' finds a friend and philosopher in 'Taarak Mehta' and often goes to him for advice whenever he is in trouble. Jethalaal's family includes his simpleton wife 'Daya Ben' (Disha Wakani) and a mischievous son 'Tapu' (Raj Anankat). Tapu is a menace and a constant source of trouble to all the members of Gokuldham. They have often warned 'Jethalaal' to reform 'Tapu' or be prepared to leave the premises.
